yes
Not very many properties here, do we plan to add more later?
No, Just the mandatory properties and then link to port collection once that is implemented.
I assume Name/PrettyName will be set later?
Yes, it is not in the development build, but should be there in final build.
we typically don't use auto here

I see them as auto in other schemas like processor.hpp.
Is there a plan to not use them now in new implementations?

We're inconsistent at best.  The thinking behind the auto policy is that the types within a commit should be immediately obvious by reading the code, and changes to the type should force diffs on everywhere that type is assumed so we can re-review for correctness and security.

make_shared is a bit of a unique case where both the type is available at the call site (in the make_shared template) and is never going to change because it's STL, so in this specific case, I tend to ignore auto when I see it in diffs.  Also, if the cleanup plans come to fruition, all these make_shared<AsyncResp> calls go away in lieu of a smarter router that has RAII built-in.

That's the long winded way of saying, I'm not worried about it either way;  If it's important to Gunnar, lets just go ahead and change it.

I don't care enough to enforce it so i'll leave it up to the author.
Most of the new commits, don't use auto here.
